      • offerTrade

        public boolean offerTrade(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> offer,
                          int sender,
                          int receiver)
        Sender makes a trade offer for any number of items to the receiver
        Parameters:
        offer: - List[Integer], posotive numbers are resources being offered, negative are resources being asked for
        sender: - int, The index of the sender in the player array
        receiver: - int, The index of the receiver in the player array
        Returns:
        Whether the trade was successfull.
        Precondition:
        The offer array must not be empty, All offered resources must be owned by the sender, All requested resources must be owned by the receiver, It must be the sender's turn, The sender and reveiver numbers must map to a player in the player array, The sender ≠ receiver
        Postcondition:
        If the receiver accepts, then the posotive resources will be given to the receiver and the negative will be given to the sender

      • endTurn

        public void endTurn()
        Switches to the next player; player 0 if currently on player 3
        Precondition:
        None
        Postcondition:
        Calls Player.endTurn(), updates the version and the if there is one. Updates the turn tracker with the status. Updates the winner if the player has won.
